    "slug": "at-first-like-a-lot-of-trauma-survivors-i-was-impatient-and-wanted-immediate-r",
    "texto": "At first, like a lot of trauma survivors, I was impatient and wanted immediate results. Once I caught myself in this behavior, I realized that it takes consistent commitment to heal patterns. After three or four months, I noticed a huge positive shift within myself. I felt a new level of happiness and contentment that I hadn't even known existed. I finally understood how my old trauma patterns had attracted drama in my present life. once I saw this dynamic, I made a conscious decision to \"Drama Detox,\" and the patterns faded away.",
